<text top="798" left="175" width="609" height="76" font="font1" id="p1_t1" reading_order_no="0" segment_no="0" tag_type="text">By  GORAN  GOLDKUHL </text>
<text top="954" left="176" width="2000" height="292" font="font2" id="p1_t2" reading_order_no="1" segment_no="1" tag_type="title">ACTION  and  MEDIA  in </text>
<text top="1158" left="182" width="2005" height="258" font="font3" id="p1_t3" reading_order_no="2" segment_no="1" tag_type="title">INTERORGANIZATIONAL </text>
<text top="1291" left="192" width="1986" height="458" font="font4" id="p1_t4" reading_order_no="3" segment_no="1" tag_type="title">INTERACTION </text>
<text top="1719" left="542" width="1242" height="84" font="font5" id="p1_t5" reading_order_no="4" segment_no="2" tag_type="text">Coordinating  the  role  of IT  with  business  procedded. </text>
<text top="1892" left="851" width="1309" height="77" font="font6" id="p1_t6" reading_order_no="5" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">he  language-action  perspective  (LAP)  has  contributed  to </text>
<text top="1964" left="850" width="1310" height="70" font="font7" id="p1_t7" reading_order_no="6" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">several  models  of  coordination  of  work.  In  the  seminal </text>
<text top="2030" left="849" width="1311" height="70" font="font7" id="p1_t8" reading_order_no="7" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">work  of  Winograd  and  Flores  [12]  the  conversation-for- </text>
<text top="2099" left="573" width="1588" height="70" font="font7" id="p1_t9" reading_order_no="8" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">action  (cfa)  scheme  was  introduced.  This  scheme  describes,  as  a </text>
<text top="2169" left="574" width="1587" height="65" font="font8" id="p1_t10" reading_order_no="9" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">kind  of  generic  construct,  how  two  actors  come  to  an  agreement </text>
<text top="2232" left="577" width="1585" height="70" font="font7" id="p1_t11" reading_order_no="10" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">about  what  is  to  be  done.  There  is  someone  who  asks  for  the  work </text>
<text top="2293" left="577" width="1582" height="77" font="font6" id="p1_t12" reading_order_no="11" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">and  someone  to  perform  the  work.  There  are  several  approaches  to </text>
<text top="2359" left="579" width="1581" height="78" font="font9" id="p1_t13" reading_order_no="12" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">business  modeling  following  the  cfa  scheme.  The  two  most  famous </text>
<text top="2433" left="580" width="1581" height="69" font="font10" id="p1_t14" reading_order_no="13" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">approaches  seem  to  be  Action  Workflow  [9]  and  DEMO  [1];  see  the </text>
<text top="2493" left="581" width="1578" height="77" font="font6" id="p1_t15" reading_order_no="14" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">article  by  Dietz  in  this  section  for  more  on  the  DEMO  methodol- </text>
<text top="2559" left="582" width="1576" height="78" font="font9" id="p1_t16" reading_order_no="15" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">ogy.  The  general  idea  is  to  get  a  business  model  of  how  people, </text>
<text top="2636" left="584" width="1576" height="66" font="font11" id="p1_t17" reading_order_no="16" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">through  conversation,  coordinate  their  work.  Such  a  business </text>
<text top="2702" left="734" width="1425" height="66" font="font11" id="p1_t18" reading_order_no="17" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">model,  focusing  on  coordination,  should  be  seen  as  founda- </text>
<text top="2761" left="733" width="1427" height="77" font="font6" id="p1_t19" reading_order_no="18" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">tional  for  the  development  of  supporting  software.  The  LAP </text>
<text top="2828" left="208" width="1287" height="78" font="font9" id="p1_t20" reading_order_no="19" segment_no="3" tag_type="text">spirit  is  to  consider  software  as  a  tool  for  coordination. </text>
